== 3. FUNDING OPPORTUNITIES (Reviewed April 2, 2026) ==

(% class="box infomessage" style="background-color:#eef3f8;border-color:#9db4cb;" %)
(((
**Applicant profile:** Open-source, non-profit (Swiss Verein in preparation), automated fact-checking tool in Alpha, solo developer. No revenue, no newsroom partnership, no EU consortium. Funding priorities: infrastructure costs, research partnerships, path to Beta.
)))

(% class="box warningmessage" %)
(((
**Reading this table:** Rows are grouped by //who can apply// (solo developer vs. research-partner-led vs. newsroom-led vs. consortium), not just by grant size. Every row ends with a concrete action and gating condition. Instruments in the Watchlist had their last known call close before April 2026 or have unverified eligibility.
)))

=== Tier A -- Solo-Actionable Now ===

These accept applications from a solo open-source developer or small Swiss nonprofit without a research partner, newsroom lead, or consortium.

|=Funder|=Amount|=Fit for FactHarbor|=Action (owner / gating condition)
|**[[NLNet Foundation>>https:~/~/nlnet.nl/]]**|EUR 5,000-50,000|Rolling open calls. Open source required. Solo developer eligible. No consortium. Proven track record funding digital commons tools.|Robert: apply to next NGI Zero Commons Fund call. No gating condition.
|**[[Innosuisse Innovation Cheque>>https:~/~/www.innosuisse.admin.ch/]]**|CHF 15,000 (100% funded)|Feasibility study with academic partner. No co-funding required. 4-6 week decision. Lowest barrier Swiss grant.|Robert: awaiting ZHAW response (Prof. Cieliebak, email sent 2026-03-25). Gated on partner confirmation.
|**[[Prototype Fund Switzerland>>https:~/~/prototypefund.opendata.ch/]]**|CHF up to 100K|Open source + public interest + Swiss. Strong fit //if// the current theme aligns (recent themes: sustainable digitalization, digital sufficiency). Not an automatic match -- requires framing around resource-efficient fact-checking.|Robert: monitor next call. Gated on theme fit and call opening.
|**[[Open Technology Fund>>https:~/~/apply.opentech.fund/]]**|$50,000-$200K|Internet freedom technologies. Rolling two-stage. Prioritizes first-time applicants. Requires framing as combating information control.|Robert: prepare application. No gating condition.

=== Tier B -- Swiss Research-Partner Path ===

These require a Swiss university research partner. The Innosuisse Cheque (Tier A) is the natural first step.

|=Funder|=Amount|=Fit for FactHarbor|=Action (owner / gating condition)
|**[[Innosuisse Innovation Project>>https:~/~/www.innosuisse.admin.ch/]]**|CHF 100K-500K|Joint R&D with university partner. 40-60% cost split, in-kind eligible. Rolling.|Gated on: Innovation Cheque completed + confirmed research partner.
|**[[BRIDGE Proof of Concept>>https:~/~/www.bridge.ch/]]**|Up to CHF 130K/year|Researcher-initiated. Academic partner must lead. 12 months.|Gated on: academic partner willing to lead. Deadlines: quarterly.
|**[[BRIDGE Discovery>>https:~/~/www.bridge.ch/]]**|Up to CHF 850K / 4 years|Scaling research. Researcher-initiated.|Gated on: established research track record with partner.
|**[[Hasler Foundation (Responsible AI)>>https:~/~/haslerstiftung.ch/]]**|CHF 50K-200K|Trustworthy AI research. Has funded claim verification before.|Gated on: research partner + research proposal.
|**[[Gebert Ruef InnoBooster>>https:~/~/www.grstiftung.ch/]]**|CHF 150K|Deep tech with market potential.|Gated on: Innosuisse or BRIDGE funding secured first.

