These require a newsroom or media organization as lead applicant. FactHarbor could be a technology partner but cannot apply solo.

|=Funder|=Amount|=Fit for FactHarbor|=Action (owner / gating condition)
|**[[Media Forward Fund>>https:~/~/www.mediaforwardfund.org/]]**|up to EUR 400K|CH/DE/AT pool, 3 rounds/year. Excludes service/technology providers, concept-stage, and sole proprietors. Requires original journalistic content + revenue.|Gated on: newsroom partner leads with FactHarbor as tech component.
|**[[Knight Foundation>>https:~/~/knightfoundation.org/]]**|$50K-$800K|Largest fact-checking funder. Rolling. Primarily US-oriented. Journalism innovation focus.|Monitor Prototype Fund and Technology Grant calls.
|**[[IFCN SUSTAIN Fund>>https:~/~/www.poynter.org/ifcn/]]**|$30,000|Requires verified IFCN signatory status. Operational support.|Gated on: IFCN signatory status (not yet achievable).
|**Ernst Goehner / JournaFONDS**|CHF 30K+|Journalism projects via Volkart/Mercator/Goehner.|Gated on: journalism project framing or newsroom partner.

